Classification.Comment: Duplications of 1p36 have been reported in individuals and families with variable phenotypes (Chen 2008, Giannikou 2012, Heilstedt 1999, Marquet 2017). In addition, one study observed enrichment of 1p36.32 and 1p36.33 gains in individuals with non-syndromic cleft lip and/or without cleft palate hypodontia (Ghazali 2021). There are no similar copy number gains spanning this region in the general populations of the Database of Genomic Variants. Thus, based upon gene content and current medical literature, this copy number variant (CNV) is interpreted as pathogenic. References: Chen et al. Am J Med Genet A. 2008 Nov 1;146A(21):2785-90.
